In this article, President Trump announces the appointment of Jeff Sessions as the new Attorney General. Trump praises Sessions for his experience and integrity, and highlights the need for a determined attorney general in these challenging times. Trump also signs three executive actions aimed at restoring safety in America, including breaking the back of criminal cartels, reducing violent crime, and stopping crimes against law enforcement officers. Sessions expresses his gratitude for the appointment and emphasizes the importance of supporting the Department of Justice and addressing the rise in crime and terrorism. He also agrees with Trump on the need for a lawful immigration system. Sessions vows to defend the Constitution and the laws of the country.